\section*{Unlicensed Assistive Personnel}

Unlicensed Assistive Personnel (UAP) are defined by the NCSBN as, "Any unlicensed person, regardless of title, who performs tasks delegated by a nurse. This includes certified nursing aides/assistants (CNAs), patient care assistants (PCAs), patient care technicians (PCTs), state tested nursing
