Nurses and health care team members are legally required to document care provided to patients. In a court of law, the rule of thumb used is, "If it wasn't documented, it wasn't done." Documentation should be objective, factual, professional, and use proper medical terminology, grammar, and spelling. All types of documentation must include the date, time, and signature of the person documenting. Any type of documentation in the EHR is considered a

