It is important to routinely evaluate the effectiveness of customized interventions for patients with cognitive impairments. Review the SMART outcomes established for each specific patient to determine if interventions are effectively promoting safety while also maintaining their physiological and psychological needs and promoting quality of life. Modify the care plan when needed to meet these outcome criteria.

