A common NANDA diagnosis related to sensory alterations is Risk for Injury, which is defined as, "Susceptible to physical damage due to environmental conditions interacting with the individual's adaptive and defensive resources, which may compromise health." "Alteration in sensation" is an associated condition for this nursing diagnosis. For risk diagnoses, there are no related factors (etiological factors) because you are identifying a vulnerability in a
